            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37363",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Please elaborate what you do.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-04T09:48:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-04T09:48:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37364",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wanderson",
                        "name": "wanderson",
                        "displayName": "Wanderson Henrique Camargo Rosa",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hello Dolf,\r\n\r\nI develop these lines in my application:\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nclass Bootstrap extends Zend_Application_Bootstrap_Bootstrap\r\n{\r\n    protected function _initView()\r\n    {\r\n        $view = new Zend_View();\r\n        $view->addHelperPath(\r\n            realpath(APPLICATION_PATH . '\/..\/library\/System\/View\/Helper'),\r\n            'System_View_Helper'\r\n        );\r\n        return $view;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nWhen I try to use any helper in that path, I receive this message exception:\r\n\r\nPlugin by name 'Substring' was not found in the registry; used paths: Admin_View_Helper_: \/path\/to\/application\/modules\/admin\/views\/helpers\/ Zend_View_Helper_: Zend\/View\/Helper\/",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wanderson",
                        "name": "wanderson",
                        "displayName": "Wanderson Henrique Camargo Rosa",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-04T10:01:32.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-04T10:01:32.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37365",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "ZF ships with a View Resource Plugin. I'd advise to use that, if you do so, you can use:\r\nresources.view.helperPath.ZendX_JQuery_View_Helper = \"ZendX\/JQuery\/View\/Helper\"\r\nresources.view.helperPathPrefix.ZendX_JQuery_View_Helper = \"ZendX_JQuery_View_Helper\"\r\n\r\nIf you want to stick to using your own init method, please see how the ZF view resource plugin does it all. This file can be found in library\/Zend\/Application\/Resource\/View.php .\r\n\r\nIf you have any problems, please comment.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-04T10:15:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-04T10:15:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37366",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wanderson",
                        "name": "wanderson",
                        "displayName": "Wanderson Henrique Camargo Rosa",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'll study this situation. I tried here with my own helper and your configurations and an exception was throwed. Sorry, but my English is too bad. I'm making miracles here.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wanderson",
                        "name": "wanderson",
                        "displayName": "Wanderson Henrique Camargo Rosa",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-04T10:29:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-04T10:29:55.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37368",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Then I'll mark this issue for now as not an issue. If it does turn out to be an issue after all (which I do not expect), please reopen this issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-04T10:54:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-04T10:54:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41805",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dragi",
                        "name": "dragi",
                        "displayName": "dragon",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I have the same problem with ZF 1.10.6\r\n\r\nI create the _initView\r\n\r\nadd the $view->->addHelperPath(dirname(..) and in the layout Zend_Loader_PluginLoader doesn't find my helper. And when I debug it, in the path there isn't my helper path.\r\n\r\nZend_Loader_PluginLoader_Exception' with message 'Plugin by name 'SearchForm' was not found in the registry;\r\n\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dragi",
                        "name": "dragi",
                        "displayName": "dragon",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-31T11:15:07.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-31T11:15:07.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41821",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wanderson",
                        "name": "wanderson",
                        "displayName": "Wanderson Henrique Camargo Rosa",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hello dragon,\r\n\r\nI'm using ZF 1.10.6 and I did this method in my Application Bootstrap:\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nprotected function _initViewHelpers()\r\n{\r\n    \/* @var $layout Zend_Layout *\/\r\n    $layout = $this->bootstrap('Layout')->getResource('Layout');\r\n\r\n    \/* @var $view Zend_View *\/\r\n    $view = $layout->getView();\r\n    $view->addHelperPath(dirname(APPLICATION_PATH)\r\n        . '\/library\/System\/View\/Helper\/', 'System_View_Helper_')\r\n\r\n    \/* More Config Options *\/\r\n}\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nCheck if this source code works for you.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wanderson",
                        "name": "wanderson",
                        "displayName": "Wanderson Henrique Camargo Rosa",
                        "active": true
                    },
